Description: Bronze nail, domed head, four-faceted shaft; tip wanting, bent, corroded.
Curator's comments: Parallels from Romna contexts in Quseir (Copeland 2011), though likely to be from an earlier context at Naukratis. Copeland, P. 2011. Metal and metal-working , in D. P. S. Peacock & L. Blue (eds), Myos Hormos - Quseir al-Qadim. Roman and Islamic ports on the Red Sea. Volume 2: Finds from the 1999-2003, Oxford: Archaeopress, BAR International Series 2286, 89-120.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (TE.008)
